items.name: Archie Panjabi
items.description:
A commission of @Zorglub.

Archie Panjabi is a British/Indian actress, mainly known for her roles in various TV shows, such as Life on Mars and The Good Wife.

1020-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my¬†usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (arch1ep4njabi:0.99), a woman as a movie star, hair upsweep updo, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"

items.name: Ralph Bakshi Style
items.description:
Ralph Bakshi is an American filmmaker and animator known for his pioneering work in adult-oriented animation and his innovative approach to storytelling.

Bakshi's style can be described as edgy, gritty, and often pushing the boundaries of traditional animation. He gained recognition for his use of a technique called rotoscoping, in which live-action footage is traced and transformed into animated sequences.

His films often address social and political issues, tackling subjects such as racism, urban life, and societal upheaval. Bakshi's storytelling is known for its raw and provocative nature, exploring complex themes through a combination of animation and live-action elements.

Some of his notable works include "Fritz the Cat," an animated feature film that became the first animated movie to receive an X rating in the United States, and "Heavy Traffic," a semi-autobiographical film that delves into the gritty realities of inner-city life.

Bakshi's films often feature a mix of realism and surrealism, combining vibrant and dynamic visuals with unconventional narratives. He has been praised for his ability to tackle controversial subjects and challenge the conventions of mainstream animation.

While Bakshi's work has sometimes been met with controversy and mixed critical reception, his contributions to the animation industry have had a lasting impact. His films paved the way for more adult-oriented animation and influenced subsequent generations of filmmakers and animators.

Ralph Bakshi's bold and unapologetic approach to storytelling and animation continues to inspire and challenge the medium, showcasing the power of animation as a vehicle for social commentary and artistic expression.

items.name: Princess Celestia (humanized)
items.description:
Princess Celestia is a character from My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic. This her humanized version.

The main trigger is princess_celestia, with optional crown and regalia.

Since a lot of high quality art of human Celestia features her nude the LoRA tends to lean toward skimpy outfits. To avoid that use nsfw, nude, or naked in the negative prompt.

Weight 0.9 - 1.0 is recommended.

Careful with aggressive negative embeddings, they tend to remove Celestia's multicolored hair.

Activation tags

1) princess_celestia is the main trigger. You might want to use purple eyes for more consistent eyes. Also crown can sometimes bleed into the image, so consider adding it into the negative if you don't want it.

2) crown has been fine-tuned to look like the crown Celestia wears in the show.

3) regalia is the necklace/choker jewelry artists tend to draw to imitate the regal harness Celestia wears in the show.

Misc.

I painstakingly painted out her horn from all images that featured it so the LoRA won't learn to generate it. I'm sorry if you actually want to have it.

Trained on 127 images (x6 repeats), with person used as a class. 8 epochs, 64 DIM / 32 Alpha. UNET 1e-4, TEXT 5e-5, Cosine with restarts 3. Base model used for training was animefull_final, but the example images were created on AbyssOrangeMix3.

My second attempt at making a LoRA. Feedback is welcome.

items.name: Victoria - Hentai University
items.description:
This is a LoRA for the character Victoria, from Hentai University a game by Noodle Jacuzzi.

Victoria's art is from the artist Oreteki18kin, the set -

Mama to Hame Chao!! Mama Man Cho! & Mama to Hame Chao!! Mama Man Cho! Natsu

I've been working my way through making these for all the characters currently in the game, and sharing them in the Discord for HU, but figured I should also put them up here.

In general, I'm working from pretty limited image sets, so expect the results to be a bit wonky at times.

I recommend a weight of around 0.5, possibly lower depending if you're combining the character LoRA with other styles/costumes/etc. along with tagging some defining characteristics of the character you're generating. Higher than that can really push the artist's original style, and may cause you issues.

All characters I train have a "character tag" added into the set to help generate them fairly reliably.

Recommended LoRA Weight - 0.5 for fairly flexible, higher if you want more of the original artist's style, lower if it doesn't play nice with other loras.

Character tag - HUVictoria
Recommended tags - brown hair, low ponytail, brown eyes, large breasts, mature female,

I may have forgotten to check and tag eye color when doing my testing, but hey. If you want it to be "set accurate" be sure to tag. Also, huge or large, take your pick on how "endowed" the principal should be.

I've got quite a backlog of these made up already, so I'll be uploading them on and off.

Check my other uploads as I put them out for more HU characters, and if you want any specific character put up soon, let me know.

items.name: Unholy
items.description:
Hello and welcome to Unholy.

Unholy is a LORA specificly oriented for character design (hard to be flexible for landscapes although didn't test it at full). It brings elements like bioluminiscence and sci-fi but can aim to fantasy due to the trained data.

The main concept was simple: Create Sci-Fi + bioluminiscence element/s/chars but in a certain trained style. This LORA is the result of several trainings, curated selections and more trainings and polishing. It was trained via Noise Offset and Multiresnoise. This is the Noise Offset. If you're curious about the multires noise I will be releasing it on June for our Patreons. And probably free here after some months. Will put an image so you can see the difference.

About the LORA:

- The trigger word is "sc3pt4" and will bring heavier the Sci-Fi aesthetics with the lighting so the values recommended are 1 and 0.7-1 but you can try lower and I suppose it will work.

- The LORA works with and without token. If you find an extreme biasing to the sci-fi you can lower the LORA's strength or you can stop using the trigger word. Both works.
- Side portrait has a different understanding due the training same as portrait. Test it yourselves.
- It was tested on 8 different models but I think Colorful v3 and Rev Animated shines more (again, this maybe cause the seed).

- Of course you can test it but again, this LORA is not intended for landscape generations.
- This LORA works good with other ones, feel free to mix (and play with "Composable Lora" if you find not mixing in the right way).

IMPORTANT!

I wrote an article here and it's like my finetunning diary for the ones interested with releases upcoming, trainings done, exclusive patreon models previews, personal thoughts, etc. So if you want to see what I'm planning or what I'm into, feel free to take a look.

Other than that, enjoy it and if you like this type of content support me and my pal in our Patreon for more quality goodies (and to pay the electricity bill):
https://www.patreon.com/user?u=90661954

Bye!

items.name: Bobby Cipher
items.description:
Bobby Cipher is a person who doesn't exist. You can use him if you need a consistent character. Please have a look at other Nobody models for contributions by other folks including those created with the LastName and NBDY tags.

Follow me if you'd like to be notified of future models!

Notes on Males

  • Turns out making a male character work is a bit more challenging than a female; all of the models I tried with this embedding seem to be really female-centric. Not surprising of course given how these models are mostly used üòä. But it does mean that randomly you'll get a female Bobby Cipher--no kidding--especially if your prompt even hints at a female subject (clothes, setting, etc). Prompting with ‚ÄúBobbyCipher, a man‚Äù can also help.

  • In my hours of trying to get good images with Bobby, it appears that a lot of men trained in the base models are classic squared-jawed (and sometimes muscly) actors or models. Not that you can't prompt away from those obviously. You also might need to prompt for color or put black and white in your negative prompt because Bobby looks a lot like classic actors from the 40s-60s.

  • I'm still exploring males, and have another embedding I'm working on, so stay tuned as I get better at doing them.

Installation

To install, download the .bin file and then place in the stable-diffusion-webui/embeddings/ folder. Then you'll either need to restart WebUI or tap the Refresh button in the Textual Inversions tab in the Extra Networks tab.

To Use

The trigger word for Automatic1111's webui is BobbyCipher which you can use in your prompt. (It should be <bobbycipher> for InvokeAI). See the gallery below for some examples.

A note about what I use to generate images

  • My main go-to photorealistic model is Avalon TRUVision V2 but I also might use RealisticVision 2.0, Protogen Infinity, or HARDBlend

  • Many of the images in the gallery use TRUVision for the initial txt2img and then RealisticVision/Protogen for a quick img2img pass with denoising set to .10 - .15 to add some additional skin texture. Unfortunately that first generation information isn't embedded into the PNG.

  • I always use the vae-ft-mse-840000 as my VAE. You can find it at HuggingFace. You can enable the VAE dropdown menu in WebUI by going to Settings -> User Interface -> Quicksettings list and adding "sd_vae"

  • When I use Hires Fix to upscale I usually use 4x-UltraSharp for the Upscaler and enable Tiled VAE which is part of the Multidiffusion Upscaler package

  • If I upscale even further in img2img I'll use a combination of ControlNet 1.1's tile_resample/tile model and Ultimate SD Upscaler

Steps: 45 (up to 55)

CFG: 7.5-8.5

Trigger Word: "gdmext luxury modern house"

Tip#1: Try to use the above Steps and CFG settings first and tweak from there. I think 40 steps may be the minimum acceptable quality. CFG 7 is minimum and after 8.5, will be a hit or a miss.

Tip#2: Using prompt "gdmext luxury modern house" works best to trigger the look, then add your own prompt to spice up the picture! However, if you want to use the raw mode, use only "gdmext" and it will reference those trained pictures without any addons.

Tip#3: This model can also produce buildings. Replace the word house with "building" to trigger this result or add words to prompt like gdmext, modern, design, building using these words in different order.

As mentioned above, this model is amazing and is heavily influenced by GDM style. So normal prompts for homes will still come out gorgeous.

As a favor, please let me know your thoughts, feedback and give a review rating. I would truly appreciate it!

items.name: Brinus - Epic Seven
items.description:
Brinus from Epic Seven

Brinus isn't in the game yet, however, she has a big fan base and she was requested a lot, so I tried my best to create a model of her regardless of how little samples are out there, so please bear with this model as it is!

Since there were so little samples to train the model, entering a weight of 0.75 will give you good results including her flying gear, however the poses will be rather limited! you can always use poseX or Control net to bypass this. If you want more flexibility with her images, you can use a weight of 0.65 and she will keep her propper look, however gear will be most likely gone.

Keyword: e7 Brinus

Suggested weight: 0.65-0.75 !important

Important Notice!!!!!

I had a new breakthrough in the training process of the loras increasing their quality and accuracy!

With this new method there's no need for heavy prompt asistance and the subject is easy to use in different situations!

For this reason I will be releasing a new version of all the models I have published so far and new models will be published with this quality! so stay tunned and check older models for updates. Thanks!

*Disclaimer: Models will be released few hours after making them so there wont be many samples published but please feel free to publish as many as you want! I love seen e7 art!
